== Introduction == The Office of the Public Prosecutor was created in the [[Autonomous communities of Spain]] by Royal Decree 1754/2007 of December 28th (BOE of December 31, 2007).
== Autonomous communities ==
=== Andalusia === The Office of the Public Prosecutor of Andalusia is more direct than the Prosecutor of the Superior Court of Justice of Andalusia, Ceuta and Melilla, which was guided by the chief prosecutor of the community.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fiscal.es/fiscal/publico/ciudadano/fiscalias_territoriales/andalucia/!ut/p/a0/04_Sj9CPykssy0xPLMnMz0vMAfGjzOI9HT0cDT2DDbwsXAwMDBwtXAI9nUJCjA3czfULsh0VAZ_oIVU!/|title=Andalusia|last=|first=|date=|website=Fiscal.es|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> Andalusia includes the provinces of [[Province of Almería|Almería]], [[Province of Cádiz|Cádiz]], [[Province of Córdoba (Spain)|Córdoba]], [[Province of Granada|Granada]], [[Province of Huelva|Huelva]], [[Province of Jaén (Spain)|Jaén]], [[Province of Málaga|Málaga]] and [[Province of Seville|Seville]].
==== Senior prosecutor (Andalusia) ==== The Office of the Public Prosecutor of Andalusia is headed by the Superior Public Prosecutor of Andalusia, Ceuta and Melilla, who assumes the representation and leadership of the Public Prosecutor's Office throughout the territory of the autonomous community—without prejudice to the powers that correspond to the Attorney General of the State. {| class="wikitable" |'''Name''' |'''Term''' |- |Jesús García Calderón |2001-2017 |- |Ana Tárrago Ruiz |2017-present |}
===== Cádiz Province (Ceuta) ===== In the Cádiz Province, the Area Prosecutor's Office of Cádiz covers the judicial party of Ceuta. The Chief Prosecutor is subordinate to the Chief Prosecutor of the Provincial Prosecutor's Office of Cádiz.
====== Chief Prosecutor (Ceuta) ====== {| class="wikitable" |+ !Name !Term |- |José Luis Puerta Martí<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.elconfidencial.com/ultima-hora-en-vivo/2014-06-03/nombrado-nuevo-teniente-fiscal-del-tribunal-constitucional_277265/|title=Nombrado nuevo teniente fiscal del Tribunal Constitucional - Martes, 03 Junio 2014 20:18|last=S.L.|first=Titania Cía. Editorial,|work=El Confidencial|access-date=2018-07-02|language=es}}</ref> |2010-present |}
===== Málaga Province (Melilla) ===== In the Málaga Province, the Area Prosecutor's Office of Melilla covers the judicial party of Melilla. The Chief Prosecutor is subordinate to the Chief Prosecutor of the Provincial Prosecutor's Office of Málaga.
====== Chief Prosecutor (Melilla) ====== {| class="wikitable" |+ !Name !Term |- |María Rodríguez García<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.diariosur.es/v/20100513/melilla/maria-rodriguez-toma-posesion-20100513.html|title=María Rodríguez toma posesión como nueva fiscal jefe de Melilla. SUR.es|last=Sur|website=www.diariosur.es|access-date=2018-07-02}}</ref> |2010-2015 |- |Isabel Martín López<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://elfarodemelilla.es/la-nueva-fiscal-jefe-de-area-asume-su-cargo-con-esfuerzo-y-compromiso/|title=La nueva fiscal jefe de Área asume su cargo con “esfuerzo y compromiso” - El Faro de Melilla|date=2015-07-27|work=El Faro de Melilla|access-date=2018-07-02|language=es-ES}}</ref> |2015-present |}
=== Aragón === The Office of the Public Prosecutor of Aragón (also referred to as the Superior Public Prosecutor of Aragón) is the judicial body that represents the Public Prosecutor's Office in the autonomous community of Aragón (Spain). It is the highest body of the Public Prosecutor's Office in the community with its headquarters in the city of Zaragoza. Aragon includes the provinces of [[Province of Huesca|Huesca]], [[Province of Teruel|Teruel]] and [[Province of Zaragoza|Zaragoza]].
